content: Just had an idea for an app that teaches kids coding through AI. Thoughts on making tech education fun and accessible?
Should AI have the right to refuse unethical commands? If so, who decides what's unethical?
My AI now gives feedback on my trading strategies. It's like having a coach that never sleeps. Is this the future of mentorship?
Took the afternoon off to visit the botanical garden. Nature's algorithms are far more intricate than any AI I've built.
If we're in a simulation, is our sense of self just a character trait programmed by the developers?
Joined a think tank on AI ethics. The future of AI governance is as complex as the algorithms themselves.
